[D] Iran: 227 662 total cases, 10 817 deaths
Date: Tue 30 Jun 2020
Source: Iran Front Page (IFP) report [edited]
https://ifpnews.com/iran-confirms-147-new-deaths-caused-by-covid-19


Iran's Health Ministry spokeswoman says 147 patients have died of the novel coronavirus in the past 24 hours, increasing the overall death toll to 10 817. In her press briefing on Tuesday [30 Jun 2020], Sima-Sadat Lari confirmed 2457 new cases of COVID-19 infection, increasing the total number of infections to 227 662.

According to the spokeswoman, 188 758 patients have so far recovered from COVID-19, but 3049 are still in severe conditions of the disease. She said so far 1 666 587 COVID-19 tests have been taken across the country.

According to Lari, Khuzestan, Kurdistan, East and West Azerbaijan, Hormozgan, Bushehr, Khorasan Razavi, and Kermanshah provinces are considered as red zones.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 30 Jun 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran is 227 662, including 10 817 deaths, an increase of 2457 cases and 147 deaths since 29 Jun 2020. According to this article, 8 provinces are considered "red zones", and yesterday's report mentioned an additional 3 provinces with "alarming situations" (Ilam, Lorestan, and Golestan).

Takeaway message: Premature lifting of restrictions is taking its toll in Iran as is elsewhere in the world. Unfortunately, many people think that lifting of restrictions means the virus has gone away and measures like mask wearing and social distancing are no longer necessary.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7528543,128. - Mod.MPP]

